For Personal Use Only Software License
A comprehensive personal-use-only software license requires careful legal drafting, clear commercial restrictions, and robust enforcement mechanisms. This analysis examines the legal landscape and provides a professionally crafted license suitable for GitHub repositories.
Legal foundation for personal-use restrictions
Personal-use-only software licenses occupy a unique position in intellectual property law, balancing accessibility for individuals with commercial protection for developers. The most successful models use revenue thresholds, activity-based definitions, and technical enforcement mechanisms rather than simple blanket commercial prohibitions.
Leading companies like TeamViewer, Unity, and JetBrains have developed sophisticated approaches to personal-use licensing. TeamViewer's AI-powered detection system identifies commercial usage patterns, while Unity implements revenue thresholds ($200,000 annually) to distinguish personal from commercial use. These models demonstrate that personal-use licenses can be both legally enforceable and commercially viable when properly structured.
The legal enforceability of personal-use restrictions depends on several critical factors: clear contract formation, proper warranty disclaimers, explicit intellectual property protection, and appropriate governing law selection. Courts have generally upheld software license restrictions when they meet standard contract law requirements and avoid unconscionable terms.
Essential legal components for enforceability
Contract formation and license grant structure
A legally sound personal-use license must establish clear contract formation with explicit license grants. The license must specify scope, limitations, and permitted uses while maintaining non-exclusive, non-transferable, and revocable terms. This prevents unauthorized distribution while protecting the licensor's intellectual property rights.
Key enforceability elements include mutual assent, consideration (even if nominal), and proper acceptance mechanisms. For GitHub repositories, this typically involves clickwrap-style acceptance through download or use, which courts have consistently upheld since ProCD v. Zeidenberg (1996).
Intellectual property protection requirements
Comprehensive IP protection requires multiple layers: copyright notices, ownership assertions, and trade secret protections. The license must explicitly state that the licensor retains all rights, title, and interest in the software while granting only specified permissions to users.
Third-party IP considerations are crucial, particularly for GitHub projects incorporating open-source components. The license must ensure compatibility with existing open-source licenses and provide appropriate attribution requirements.
Liability and warranty disclaimers
Proper "AS IS" disclaimers and liability limitations are essential for legal protection. The license must disclaim implied warranties of merchantability and fitness for particular purpose, typically using conspicuous capital letters or prominent formatting to ensure enforceability.
Liability caps should limit damages to license fees paid (if any) and explicitly exclude consequential damages, lost profits, and business interruption. This protects developers from potentially unlimited liability exposure.
Commercial use restriction methodologies
Defining commercial versus personal use
The most effective personal-use licenses combine multiple definitional approaches rather than relying on single criteria. Activity-based definitions prove more enforceable than simple revenue thresholds because they address the actual use context rather than just user characteristics.
Commercial use should encompass any activity that generates revenue, provides business advantage, or occurs within a commercial environment. This includes home office use for business purposes, professional service provision, and internal business operations regardless of profit generation.
Personal use definitions should focus on individual, non-commercial activities: learning, experimentation, personal projects, and assistance to family/friends without compensation. The key distinction lies in purpose and context rather than just user identity.
Revenue thresholds and organizational limits
Revenue-based thresholds provide clear, measurable boundaries that users can easily understand and comply with. The $200,000 annual revenue threshold used by Unity represents current industry best practice, balancing accessibility for small organizations with commercial protection for larger entities.
Employee count thresholds offer an alternative approach, typically ranging from 100-500 employees for small business exemptions. This method addresses organizations with high revenue but limited software budgets, though it requires more complex verification mechanisms.
Enforcement mechanisms and violation consequences
Technical enforcement through license servers, usage monitoring, and algorithmic detection provides the most effective compliance assurance. TeamViewer's AI-powered detection system demonstrates how sophisticated monitoring can identify commercial usage patterns while minimizing false positives.
Contractual audit rights should include reasonable notice periods (30-90 days), annual frequency limits, and third-party auditor provisions. Violation consequences should include retroactive licensing fees, penalty multipliers (2-5x regular costs), and termination rights.
GitHub-specific implementation considerations
License file structure and detection
GitHub's licensing ecosystem strongly favors standard license formats for automatic detection and display. Custom licenses should use the filename "LICENSE" (without extension) in the repository root directory to maximize visibility and platform integration.
The Licensee gem used by GitHub compares license files against known templates using multiple matching strategies. Custom licenses often appear as "Other" or unrecognized, reducing discoverability through GitHub's search filters.
Documentation and community communication
Clear licensing documentation in README files is essential for custom licenses since GitHub's automatic detection may not recognize personal-use restrictions. Users need explicit guidance on permitted uses, commercial restrictions, and compliance requirements.
The documentation should include plain-language explanations of licensing terms, contact information for licensing questions, and specific examples of permitted and prohibited uses. This reduces ambiguity and supports enforcement efforts.
Professional legal framework: Personal-Use-Only Software License
The following license incorporates best practices from legal research, industry precedents, and GitHub compatibility requirements:

PERSONAL-USE-ONLY SOFTWARE LICENSE
Version 1.0
Copyright Â© 2025 4MioDio. All rights reserved.
1. DEFINITIONS
"Software" means the computer program(s), source code, object code, documentation, and any modifications or derivative works thereof covered by this License.
"You" or "Your" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.
"Personal Use" means use by an individual for personal, non-commercial purposes including learning, experimentation, personal projects, and assistance to family and friends without monetary compensation.
"Commercial Use" means any use that: (a) generates revenue or monetary compensation; (b) occurs within a business or commercial environment; (c) provides professional services to third parties; (d) supports business operations or commercial activities; or (e) creates competitive advantage for any organization.
2. LICENSE GRANT
Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the copyright holder hereby grants You a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable license to use, copy, modify, and distribute the Software solely for Personal Use.
3. RESTRICTIONS
You may NOT:

Use the Software for Commercial Use as defined above
Distribute or sublicense the Software to others for Commercial Use
Remove or modify copyright notices or license terms
Use the Software in any server or multi-user environment for business purposes
Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software except as expressly permitted by law

4. COMMERCIAL USE PROHIBITION
Commercial Use is strictly prohibited under this License. Commercial users must obtain a separate commercial license from the copyright holder. Revenue thresholds or organizational size do not exempt users from this restriction.
5. OWNERSHIP AND INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
The copyright holder retains all rights, title, and interest in and to the Software. This License does not grant You any rights to trademarks, service marks, or other intellectual property of the copyright holder.
6. TERMINATION
This License is effective until terminated. Your rights under this License will terminate automatically without notice if You fail to comply with any term hereof. Upon termination, You must cease all use of the Software and destroy all copies in Your possession.
7. COMPLIANCE AND AUDIT
The copyright holder reserves the right to verify compliance with this License through reasonable means, including but not limited to usage monitoring and periodic audits with thirty (30) days' written notice.
8. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE COPYRIGHT HOLDER BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT, OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.
9. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
IN NO EVENT SHALL THE COPYRIGHT HOLDER BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, OR USE, INCURRED BY YOU OR ANY THIRD PARTY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT OR TORT, EVEN IF THE COPYRIGHT HOLDER HAS BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.
10. GOVERNING LAW
This License shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Florida, without regard to its conflict of laws principles. Any disputes arising under this License shall be resolved exclusively in the courts of the State of Florida.
11. ENTIRE AGREEMENT
This License constitutes the entire agreement between the parties concerning the Software and supersedes all prior agreements and understandings relating to the subject matter hereof.
